K8s Architecture

Master Node

1) Kube API Server
- Manage & control the entire cluster.
- It orchestrates the communication between control plane components such as:
  kube-controller, kube-scheduler, kube-proxy & etcd key-value store.
- Using kubectl CLI tool, we can interact with kube-apiserver.

Controller Objects (apps/v1)
- Pod, PVC, PV, CM, Secret, SA
- Deployment, DaemonSet

2) Kube Scheduler
- It is a component of the K8s control plane that is responsible for making decisions
  about where to place newly created Pods within the cluster.
- Ensures the workloads are distributed across nodes.

3) Kube Controller
Controllers:
1. Deployment Controller
2. StatefulSet Controller
3. Job Controller
4. Service Controller
5. Ingress Controller
6. Namespace Controller
7. DaemonSet Controller
8. Persistent Volume Controller

4) ETCD
- It is a key-value store, open-source database.
- It maintains the complete configuration and state of the K8s cluster
  (like number of nodes, pods).
- Stores hardware configuration info.

----------------------------------------

Worker Node

Kubelet    -- its just a binary not deploy or daemon
- Runs on every node in a cluster.
- Responsible for managing containers on the node and ensuring they run in a healthy state.

Kube-Proxy       -- Daemonset
- Network proxy & load balancer that runs on each node.
- Responsible for maintaining network rules on nodes.
- Helps expose services to the network.

Container Runtime

1) Responsible for executing & managing the containerized application on a host system.
2) Container runtime handles tasks such as creating, starting, stopping & deleting containers.
3) Popular container runtimes include Docker Engine, containerd, CRI-O.

-------------------------------------------------
Container (Docker Container)

Container Image
1) It is a lightweight & portable package that can run in any environment.
2) It consists of multiple layers that can run within the container runtime environment
   such as Docker or containerd. Images are built from a Dockerfile.
3) It is lightweight & portable, so you can run in all environments.
   It encapsulates the application & its dependency (app code, base image & dependencies)
   and makes it easily transportable.

